This paper proposes a novel decision tree ensemble approach for conversion rate prediction in recommendation systems. The proposed method leverages deep cascade structures and gradient boosting decision trees to effectively learn feature representation. The paper also discusses ensemble learning and an improved feature learning method. Based on these characteristics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) due to the use of decision trees and feature representation.
